<!-- Progress — spec card render
     Source spec: ds-architect-agent/children/components/feedback.md#progress -->
<div class="dst-component-card">
  <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-2">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Progress</h3>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 font-mono">2 variants · 3 sizes · 2 states</p>
  </div>
  <p class="dst-component-intro">Progress indicator. Linear bar (file uploads, multi-step forms) and circular (page-level loading, sparser visual).</p>

  <div class="dst-spec-row">
    <span class="dst-spec-label">Variants</span>
    <div class="dst-spec-values">
      <span class="dst-spec-pill dst-pill-variant">linear</span>
      <span class="dst-spec-pill dst-pill-variant">circular</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="dst-spec-row">
    <span class="dst-spec-label">Sizes</span>
    <div class="dst-spec-values">
      <span class="dst-spec-pill dst-pill-size">sm · 4px / 24px</span>
      <span class="dst-spec-pill dst-pill-size">md · 6px / 40px</span>
      <span class="dst-spec-pill dst-pill-size">lg · 8px / 64px</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="dst-spec-row">
    <span class="dst-spec-label">States</span>
    <div class="dst-spec-values">
      <span class="dst-spec-pill dst-pill-state">determinate</span>
      <span class="dst-spec-pill dst-pill-state">indeterminate</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="dst-spec-note"><strong>Pair rule:</strong> always pair with a numeric label nearby ("32 of 100" for determinate, "Loading…" for indeterminate). A bar without context is just decoration. <strong>Indeterminate:</strong> use ONLY when total is unknown — for measurable progress, an indeterminate bar feels deceptive.</div>
</div>
